PrecisAppointment of DAVID ADAM as Ambassador of Canada to the Republic of Ecuador; WILLIAM L. CLARKE as Ambassador of Canada to the Kingdom of Sweden; ANN COLLINS as Consul General of Canada in St-Petersburg; MICHEL de SALABERRY as Ambassador of Canada to the Hashemite Kindgom of Jordan; GILLES DUGUAY as Ambassador of Canada to the Republic of Romania and to the Republic of Moldova; BERNARD DUSSAULT as High Commissioner for Canada to the Republic of Kenya; YVES GAGNON as Ambassador of Canada to the Republic of Venezuela and to the Dominican Republic; PIERRE GIGUÈRE as Ambassador of Canada to the Republic of Cameroon and to the Central African Republic; ROLAND GOULET as Ambassador of Canada to the Eastern Republic of Uruguay; GEORGE HAYNAL as Consul General of Canada in New York and Commissioner for Canada in Bermuda; LOUISE LÉGER as Ambassador of Canada to the Republic of Panama; GABRIEL-M. LESSARD as Ambassador of Canada to Ethiopia and to Eritrea; EDWARD LIPMAN as Consul General of Canada in Shanghai; D. GORDON LONGMUIR as Ambassador of Canada to the Kingdom of Cambodia; FRANÇOIS MATHYS as Ambassador of Canada to the Kingdom of Norway and to the Republic of Iceland; SUSAN McCOY as Ambassador of Canada to the Republic of Mali; MARK MOHER as Alternate Permanent Representative and Ambassador of Canada to the Office of the United Nations and Permanent Representative to the United Nations for Disarmament; ARTHUR C. PERRON as High Commissioner for Canada to the Republic of South Africa; MARC PERRON as Ambassador of Canada to the United Mexican States; JEAN-GUY SAINT-MARTIN as Ambassador of Canada to the Kingdom of Morocco; KONRAD SIGURDSON as High Commissioner for Canada to the Democratic Socialist Republic of Sri Lanka and High Commissioner for Canada to the Republic of Maldives; and JOHN WEEKES as Permanent Representative and Ambassador of Canada to the Office of the United Nations and to the World Trade Organization.
